com.yworks.yfiles.graph

Interface IMapper<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - The type of element this interface accepts as keys for the mapping.
    V - The type of element this interface accepts as values for the mapping.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CreationProperties, Mapper

    public interface IMapper<K,V>
    An interface for simple typed dictionary-like implementations.

    IMappers are most prominently used when interfacing with layout algorithms and GraphML. IGraph also provides the MapperRegistry to add additional information to a graph.

    Using IMapper is described in the section Associating Data with Graph Elements.

    See Also:
    Mappers, Mapper

        static <K,V> IMapper<K,V> fromFunction(Function<K,V> getter)
        Create an implementation of IMapper that delegates getValue(java.lang.Object) getter calls to the provided handler.

        The implementation returned silently ignores calls to the getValue(java.lang.Object) setter.

        Type Parameters:

        V - The type of the value to use.

        Returns:

      • getValue

        V getValue(K key)
        Gets the value for a given key in the mapping.

        Setting a value for an already existing key overwrites the previous value.

        It depends on the specific implementation of the mapper whether a mapping can be removed. If an implementation provides a way to remove a mapping, that should be preferred over setting a null value. For example, Mapper provides the Mapper.removeValue(java.lang.Object) method.

        Parameters:
        key - The key of the mapping.
        Returns:
        The value.
        See Also:
        setValue(java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object)
